<div style="background:#E3F2FD;border:1px solid #1976D2;border-radius:4px;padding:15px 20px;margin-bottom:20px;font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;">
    <strong style="font-size:14px;color:#1565C0;">How AI Prompts Work</strong>
    <p style="margin:8px 0 0;">
        AI Prompts are the instructions sent to the AI provider (Claude, OpenAI, etc.) when generating meta titles and descriptions.
        Each prompt is a template with <strong>placeholders</strong> like <code>{{name}}</code>, <code>{{sku}}</code>, <code>{{price}}</code>
        that get replaced with actual entity data before being sent to the AI.
    </p>
    <ol style="margin:8px 0 0;padding-left:20px;">
        <li>Create or edit prompts for different entity types (Product, Category, CMS Page)</li>
        <li>Mark one prompt as <strong>"Default"</strong> per entity type &mdash; it will be used automatically for AI generation jobs</li>
        <li>Customize the tone, rules, and output format to match your brand and SEO strategy</li>
        <li>The prompt <strong>must</strong> instruct the AI to return JSON: <code>{"title":"...","description":"..."}</code></li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin:8px 0 0;color:#555;">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Use the "Product - E-commerce Focused" prompt for conversion-optimized copy,
        or the "Product - Minimal/Short" prompt for lower token usage and faster generation.
    </p>
</div>
